'''Eldor Azamat oʻgʻli Shomurodov''' (born 29 June 1995) is an Uzbek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|forward]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

Shomurodov played in his homeland for [[Mash'al Mubarek]] and [[FC Bunyodkor|Bunyodkor]], before spending three years with [[FC Rostov|Rostov]] in the [[Russian Premier League]]. In 2020, he moved to [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]] in Serie A for €8 million and a year later Roma for €17.5 million, followed by loan spells at [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] and [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].

After helping the [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|under-20 team]] to the quarter-finals of the [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], Shomurodov made his full international debut for Uzbekistan later that year, and represented the country at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]. He also captained his team as they qualified for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], Uzbekistan's first ever appearance at the tournament. With 44 goals, he is the nation's [[Uzbekistan national football team#Top goalscorers|all-time top scorer]].

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
Shomurodov was born in [[Jarqoʻrgʻon]], [[Uzbekistan]] on 29 June 1995. His father, uncles, and brother are also footballers. His uncles, Ilkhom and [[Otabek Shamuradov|Otabek]] Shomurodov, both played for [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]]. Eldor started playing football at six years old and at the age of eleven joined the academy for [[Mash'al Mubarek]]. At the beginning of 2015 he transferred to [[FC Bunyodkor|Bunyodkor]]. On 15 July 2017, he moved to the [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Rostov|Rostov]]. His most prolific season for the club was his last, with 11 goals in [[2019–20 Russian Premier League|2019–20]].<ref name=":0"/>

===Genoa===
On 1 October 2020, Shomurodov completed an €8 million move to [[Serie A]] club [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]]. He became the second Uzbek to play in Serie A, after [[Ilyos Zeytulayev]], whose teams also included Genoa.<ref name=":0"/> He made his debut on 19 October in a goalless draw at [[Hellas Verona]], being substituted for [[Gianluca Scamacca]] after 63 minutes;<ref>{{cite news |date=19 October 2020 |title=Serie A, Perin salva il Genoa, contro il Verona finisce 0-0 |trans-title=Serie A, Perin saves Genoa, match against Verona ends 0-0 |url=https://www.eurosport.it/calcio/serie-a/2020-2021/serie-a-perin-salva-il-genoa-contro-il-verona-finisce-0-0_sto7957963/story.shtml |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=Eurosport |language=Italian}}</ref> his first goal on 30 November was consolation in a 2–1 home loss to [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gervinho at the double for Parma |url=https://jerseyeveningpost.com/uksport/2020/11/30/gervinho-at-the-double-for-parma/ |access-date=13 May 2023 |work=Jersey Evening Post |date=30 November 2020}}</ref> He scored eight times in his one season at the [[Stadio Luigi Ferraris]], including two in a 4–3 home loss to [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] on 15 May 2021.<ref>{{cite news |title=Soccer-Atalanta clinch Champions League spot with Genoa win |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-gen-att-report-idUKKCN2CW0EQ |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=Reuters |date=15 May 2021}}</ref>

=== Roma ===
On 2 August 2021, [[AS Roma|Roma]] announced the acquisition of Shomurodov on a five-year contract for €17.5 million plus bonuses.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/official-shomurodov-sold-to-roma/ |title=Official: Shomurodov sold to Roma |last=Campanale |first=Susy |date=2 August 2021 |publisher=Football Italia |accessdate=7 August 2021}}</ref> He debuted 17 days later in [[José Mourinho]]'s first game as manager, away to [[Trabzonspor]] in the first leg of the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League qualifying phase and play-off round (Main Path)|UEFA Europa Conference League play-off round]]. He started the game and scored the decisive goal of a 2–1 win, becoming at 26 years the second{{efn|3 weeks after [[Igor Sergeev (Uzbekistani footballer)|Igor Sergeev]]}} and youngest Uzbek to score in the [[UEFA Conference League]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Carci |first1=Francesco |title=Conference League, Trabzonspor-Roma 1-2: decide, buona la prima europea di Mourinho|trans-title=Conference League, Trabzonspor-Roma 1-2: decides, Mourinho's European debut a good one|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/coppe/2021/08/19/news/conference_league_trabzonspor-roma_1-2_shomurodov_decisivo_buona_la_prima_per_mourinho-314617230/ |access-date=30 August 2021 |work=[[La Repubblica]] |date=19 August 2021 |language=Italian}}</ref> Mainly a substitute in his first season, he scored three league goals, starting with an equaliser in a 3–2 loss at [[Venezia F.C.|Venezia]] on 7 November.<ref>{{cite news |title=Soccer-Venezia stun Roma with comeback to win five-goal thriller |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-vnz-rom-report-idUKKBN2HS08N |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=Reuters |date=7 November 2021}}</ref> He went on to become the first-ever Uzbek football player to win a major UEFA competition, as his club triumphed in the [[2022 UEFA Europa Conference League Final]], for which he was a last-minute substitute.<ref>{{cite news |title=Statistics on Conference League final |url=https://www.iffhs.com/posts/1913 |date=26 May 2022}}</ref>

On 8 September 2022, during a [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League group stage]] game against [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]], [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] lost 1-2 to [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] and he scored one goal, becoming at 27 years [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan’s]] oldest goalscorer ever in [[UEFA Europa League]] final stage, a record that still stands.<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Ludogorets 2-1 Roma |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2035977--ludogorets-vs-roma/ |website=UEFA |access-date=1 February 2025}}</ref>

On 30 January 2023, [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] signed Shomurodov on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |author=Giulio Cardone |author2=Enrico De Lellis |date=30 January 2023 |title=Calciomercato, le ultime news di oggi: Zaniolo tentato dal Siviglia, Shomurodov allo Spezia |trans-title=Transfer market, today's latest news: Zaniolo tempted by Sevilla, Shomurodov to Spezia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/mercato/2023/01/30/diretta/calciomercato_serie_a_ultime_news-385700762/ |access-date=30 January 2023 |work=La Repubblica |language=it}}</ref>

On 27 July 2023, [[Cagliari Calcio]], a team that had [[2022–23 Cagliari Calcio season|recently been promoted]] to [[Serie A]], announced the signing of Shomurodov from Roma on a season-long loan with an option to make the move permanent.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 July 2023 |title=Shomurodov è del Cagliari |trans-title=Shomurodov is of Cagliari |url=https://www.cagliaricalcio.com/news/ultimissime/22951/shomurodov-e-del-cagliari-prestito-con-diritto-di-riscatto |access-date=27 July 2023 |website=www.cagliaricalcio.com |language=it |archive-date=28 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230728022700/http://www.cagliaricalcio.com/news/ultimissime/22951/shomurodov-e-del-cagliari-prestito-con-diritto-di-riscatto |url-status=dead }}</ref> He returned to Roma after the end of his loan to Cagliari in summer 2024.

On 30 January 2025, during the 8th and last day of the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League league phase]], he scored a goal against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], becoming at 29 years the oldest Uzbek to score in an [[UEFA club competitions|UEFA club competition]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Roma vs Eintracht Frankfurt |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/roma-vs-eintracht-frankfurt-uefa-europa-league-2024-25 |website=AS Roma |access-date=4 February 2025}}</ref> AS Roma won the game 2–0. During the second half of the 2024–25 season Eldor had fruitful games by scoring goals and with assists both at Serie A and Europa League.

===İstanbul Başakşehir===
On 10 July 2025, Shomurodov was loaned by [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] in Turkey, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=İstanbul Başakşehir|url=https://ibfk.com.tr/haberler/hos-geldin-eldor-shomurodov|title=HOŞ GELDİN ELDOR SHOMURODOV|trans-title=WELCOME ELDOR SHOMURODOV|date=10 July 2025|access-date=12 July 2025|language=tr}}</ref> On 22 April 2026, the move was converted into a permanent transfer following İstanbul Başakşehir’s retention of top-division status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://romapress.net/shomurodov-officially-leaves-roma-on-permanent-deal/|title=Shomurodov officially leaves Roma on permanent deal|date=22 April 2026|website=romapress.net}}</ref> He finished his debut season at the club with 22 goals, ending as the [[2025–26 Süper Lig|league]]'s joint top scorer alongside [[Paul Onuachu]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uzdaily.uz/en/shomurodov-tops-turkish-super-lig-scoring-list-2026/ |title=Shomurodov Tops Turkish Super Lig Scoring List 2026 |publisher=uzdaily.uz |date=18 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==

=== Youth ===
Shomurodov played for the [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|Uzbekistan U19]] in the [[2014 AFC U-19 Championship]] and qualified to [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. He played in all five matches of U-20 team at the 2015 U-20 World Cup and scored two goals for the quarter-finalists.<ref name=fifa/>

Shomurodov and two teammates were listed as nominees for best young players of Asia by AFC in 2015.{{Citation needed|date=January 2022}}[[File:TUR-UZB 20190113 Asian Cup 9.jpg|thumb|Eldor Shomurodov (№14) at 2019 Asian Cup]]

=== Senior ===
Shomurodov was called to play for the [[Uzbekistan national football team|senior national team]] on 3 September 2015 for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] qualifying match against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]]. He made his official debut in that match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=275171/match=300317520/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623001753/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=275171/match=300317520/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=23 June 2015|title=Uzbekistan- Yemen, 2015-09-03|publisher= FIFA |date=3 September 2015}}</ref> On 8 October 2015, he scored his first goal for the national team in a World Cup qualifying away match against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]], securing a 4–0 victory for the Uzbek side.{{Citation needed|date=January 2022}} Shomurodov was part of the squad that manager [[Héctor Cúper]] took to the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] in the United Arab Emirates. He came off the bench to score a late winner in a 2–1 opening victory over [[Oman national football team|Oman]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Eldor Shomurodov secures a 2-1 win for Uzbekistan over Oman |url=https://sports.uz/en/news/view/eldor-shomurodov-secures-a-2-1-win-for-uzbekistan-over-oman-09-01-2019 |access-date=30 August 2021 |publisher=Sports.uz |date=9 January 2019}}</ref> and followed it by scoring twice in a 4–0 win over neighbours [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] as a starter.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ridge |first1=Patric |title=Turkmenistan 0 Uzbekistan 4: Group F leader cruises into Asian Cup last-16 |url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/asian-cup-2019/afc-asian-cup-report-group-f-uzbekistan-turkmenistan-hector-cuper/article25987227.ece |access-date=30 August 2021 |work=The Hindu |date=14 January 2019}}</ref> In the last group game, he opened a 2–1 loss to [[Japan national football team|Japan]] as both teams progressed.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Immobile |first=Ciro |date=2025-04-29 |title=kubet |url=https://ku-bets.io |access-date=2025-05-02 |website=ku-bets.io |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=AFC Asian Cup 2019: Tsukasa Shiotani screamer as new-look Japan too much for Uzbekistan |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/football/afc-asian-cup-2019-tsukasa-shiotani-screamer-as-new-look-japan-too-much-for-uzbekistan/story-nYoZJFlRPFnyDk6QgvSvhJ.html |access-date=30 August 2021 |work=Hindustan Times |agency=AFP |date=17 January 2019}}</ref> On 29 March 2022, Shomurodov scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 4–2 win over [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] in the [[Nowruz Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite news |title=Uganda: AS Roma's Shomurodov nets a hat-trick in Navruz Cup final |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/en/all-african-countries/uganda-as-romas-shomurodov-nets-a-hat-trick-in-navruz-cup-final/ |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=Sport News Africa |date=31 March 2022}}</ref> He added another three goals on 11 June against the [[Maldives national football team|Maldives]] in a [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] qualifier;<ref>{{cite news |title=Uzbekistan cruised to a 4-0 win over Maldives |url=https://www.uzdaily.uz/en/post/73622 |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=UZ Daily |date=11 June 2022}}</ref> his ten goals in that successful qualification campaign made him the second highest scorer behind [[Ali Mabkhout]] of the United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{cite news |title=India grouped with Australia, Uzbekistan, Syria for AFC Asian Cup 2023 |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/india-ind/story/4945274/india-group-afc-asian-cup-2023-australia-uzbekistan-syria |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=ESPN |date=11 May 2023}}</ref> On 14 June 2023, Shomurodov scored a brace in a 2–0 victory over [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] during the [[2023 CAFA Nations Cup|CAFA Nations Cup]], in which he became his country's all-time top scorer with 36 goals, breaking previous record of [[Maxim Shatskikh]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/more/cafa_nations_cup/news/eldor_shomurodov_breaks_uzbekistan_scoring_record.html |title=Eldor Shomurodov breaks Uzbekistan scoring record |publisher=AFC |date=15 June 2023 }}</ref>

Shomurodov missed out on the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] due to a leg injury, in which Uzbekistan reached the quarter-finals.

==== 2024 Olympics ====
[[File:Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympic men's association football, 2024-07-24 (248).jpg|thumb|Eldor Shomurodov scoring at the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].]]

Shomurodov was included in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads#Uzbekistan|squad]] for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Olympic Games]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Football - Hommes - Ouzbékistan |url=https://olympics.com/fr/paris-2024/equipe/uzbekistan_fblmteam11--uzb01 |website=Olympics.com |access-date=25 July 2024}}</ref> Uzbekistan’s first participation to the [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Football Tournament]]. On 24 July 2024, during the first group stage match against Spain, he scored Uzbekistan’s first ever goal in the Olympic history, from the penalty spot.<ref>{{cite web |title=PARIS 2024 OLYMPICS: SPAIN OPEN MEN'S CAMPAIGN WITH 2-1 VICTORY OVER UZBEKISTAN |url=https://olympics.com/en/news/paris-2024-olympics-spain-mens-football-2-1-victory-uzbekistan |website=Omympics.com |access-date=25 July 2024}}</ref>

==== 2025 ====
On 5 June 2025, his captaincy saw Uzbekistan qualify for the 2026 FIFA World Cup for the first time in its history, following a draw against the United Arab Emirates in the 9th matchday of Asian qualifiers.<ref>{{Cite web |last=He |first=Fred |date=6 June 2025 |title=Rising Uzbekistan secure soccer World Cup debut, first ever Central Asian nation to qualify |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2025/06/06/sport/uzbekistan-uae-world-cup-qualifiers-soccer-intl-hnk |access-date=8 June 2025 |website=CNN}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Shomurodov is a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] capable of both scoring and providing assists and who can vary across the offensive front.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 August 2021 |title=10 cose da sapere su Eldor Shomurodov |trans-title=10 things to know about Eldor Shomurodov |url=https://www.asroma.com/it/notizie/2021/08/10-cose-da-sapere-su-eldor-shomurodov |access-date=30 January 2023 |language=it |archive-date=3 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003001324/https://www.asroma.com/it/notizie/2021/08/10-cose-da-sapere-su-eldor-shomurodov |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=4 August 2021 |title=Roma, ecco Shomurodov: duttilità e prospettiva per l'attacco giallorosso |trans-title=Roma, here is Shomurodov: versatility and potential for the Giallorossi attack. |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/fantanews/04-08-2021/roma-shomurodov-pragmatismo-prospettiva-attacco-giallorosso-420180524914.shtml |access-date=30 January 2023 |language=it}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=17 October 2020 |title=Genoa, Shomurodov: chi è, perché prenderlo al fantacalcio |trans-title=Genoa, Shomurodov: who he is, why to pick him for fantasy football |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/fantanews/17-10-2020/genoa-shomurodov-chi-perche-prenderlo-fantacalcio-39063472184.shtml |access-date=30 January 2023 |language=it}}</ref> Shomurodov is capable of strong accelerations and progressions on the run,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ho fatto bene a prendere Shomurodov al Fantacalcio? – Ultimo Uomo |trans-title=Did I do well to pick Shomurodov in Fantasy Football? – Ultimo Uomo |url=https://www.ultimouomo.com/fatto-bene-prendere-shomurodov-fantacalcio-genoa-serie-a |access-date=2025-05-02 |website=www.ultimouomo.com |language=it}}</ref> and he is physically strong, he can attack space, has dynamism and is skilled in aerial play.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 October 2020 |title="Grifo uzbeko", Zeytualaev: «Shomurodov? Forte di testa, gran fisico e generoso: somiglia a Milik |trans-title="Uzbek Grifo," Zeytualaev: "Shomurodov? Strong in the air, great physique, and generous: he resembles Milik." |url=https://www.ilsecoloxix.it/sport/2020/10/06/news/grifo-uzbeko-zeytualaev-shomurodov-forte-di-testa-gran-fisico-e-generoso-somiglia-a-milik-1.39389543 |access-date=30 January 2023 |language=it}}</ref>

For his quality his nickname is "the Uzbek [[Lionel Messi|Messi]]".<ref name=":0"/> He studied the games of [[Didier Drogba]] and [[Fernando Torres]] as a child.<ref name=fifa>{{cite news |title=Free-scoring Shomurodov out to make history with Uzbekistan |url=https://www.fifa.com/news/free-scoring-shomurodov-out-to-make-history-with-uzbeksitan |access-date=13 May 2023 |publisher=FIFA |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>

